edu.umd.cs.dmonner.tweater.finder
Class FinderWorker

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Thread
      edu.umd.cs.dmonner.tweater.finder.FinderWorker
All Implemented Interfaces:
FinderWorkerControl, java.lang.Runnable, java.rmi.Remote
public class FinderWorker
extends java.lang.Thread
implements FinderWorkerControl

Receives status IDs to look up from a Finder instance and uses the Twitter REST API to find complete information about these statuses. Reports this information back to the calling Finder instance.

Author:
dmonner

enqueue

public void enqueue(java.util.List<java.lang.Long> status_ids)
Description copied from interface: FinderWorkerControl
Adds to the queue a list of status IDs that this worker will attempt to find. Good practice says that the number of status IDs submitted should be the same as the result of the want method.

Specified by:
enqueue in interface FinderWorkerControl

want

public int want()
Specified by:
want in interface FinderWorkerControl
Returns:
The number of status IDs that this worker wants. This number is equal to the number of outstanding Twitter REST API requests remaining minus the current size of the queue.
